TITLE: Defining Patient Access with Account Compartment in JS
DESCRIPTION: This access policy grants read-only access to Patient resources within a customer's "account" compartment. Any resource created or updated will be tagged with `meta.account` set to `Organization/abc-123`, and read/search operations will filter on this tag.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/access/access-policies.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
  "resourceType": "AccessPolicy",
  "name": "Patient Example",
  // Any resource created or updated will be tagged with `meta.account` set to `Organization/abc-123`
  "compartment": {
    "reference": "Organization/abc-123",
    "display": "Example Customer Organization"
  },
  "resource": [
  // Any read or search operation will filter on `meta.account` equals `Organization/abc-123`
    {
      "resourceType": "Patient",
      "criteria": "Patient?_compartment=Organization/abc-123"
      "readonly": true
    }
  ]
}
```

