TITLE: Obtain OAuth2 Token using Python
DESCRIPTION: This Python function `get_auth_token` sends a POST request to the specified URL to obtain an access token using the Client Credentials Flow. It takes the token endpoint URL, client ID, and client secret as input, encodes the client ID and secret in the request body, and returns the access token from the JSON response. The `requests` library is required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/auth/methods/client-credentials.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def get_auth_token(url, client_id, client_secret):

  # Encode the client ID and client secret
  headers = {
      "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
  }
  body = {
      "grant_type": "client_credentials",
      "client_id": client_id,
      "client_secret": client_secret
  }

  response = requests.post(url, data=body, headers=headers)
  return response.json()['access_token']
```

