TITLE: SearchRequest Interface in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure of a `SearchRequest` object, which is the internal representation of a FHIR search query.  It includes properties for resource type, filters, sort rules, offset, count, fields, name, total, include and revInclude parameters and their datatypes.  This interface is used by the server and client-side applications to facilitate common handling of searches.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/contributing/search-architecture.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
interface SearchRequest {
  readonly resourceType: string;
  filters?: {
    code: string;
    operator: Operator;
    value: string;
  }[];
  sortRules?: {
    code: string;
    descending?: boolean;
  }[];
  offset?: number;
  count?: number;
  fields?: string[];
  name?: string;
  total?: 'none' | 'estimate' | 'accurate';
  include?: IncludeTarget[];
  revInclude?: IncludeTarget[];
  summary?: 'true' | 'text' | 'data';
}
```

