TITLE: System Level FHIR Export in Python
DESCRIPTION: This Python code demonstrates how to perform a system-level export of all FHIR resources in a Medplum project.  It shows how to obtain credentials, setup the HTTP headers and make the API call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/api/fhir/operations/bulk-fhir.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from medplum import MedplumClient


async def main():
    # To run this example, you need a Medplum project with a client application.
    # First, create a client application in Medplum.
    # Then, grant the client application the 'Bulk Data Access' permission.
    # Finally, set the following environment variables:
    # MEDPLUM_CLIENT_ID: The client ID of the client application.
    # MEDPLUM_CLIENT_SECRET: The client secret of the client application.
    # MEDPLUM_BASE_URL: The base URL of your Medplum server.
    client = MedplumClient()

    # You can optionally override the default parameters
    # See: https://www.hl7.org/fhir/uv/bulkdata/STU2/export.html for parameter details.
    params = {
        '_outputFormat': 'application/fhir+ndjson',
        '_since': '2023-01-01T00:00:00Z',
        '_type': 'Patient,Observation'
    }

    bulk_data_export = await client.bulk_export(params)

    print(f'BulkDataExport Job: {bulk_data_export}')


if __name__ == '__main__':
    import asyncio
    asyncio.run(main())
```

