TITLE: Updating FHIR Resource Fields with REST PATCH
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet uses the Medplum client to perform a targeted, field-level update to a Task resource using the HTTP PATCH method. It includes a `test` operation to ensure that the task has not been modified on the server before applying the changes. This approach is useful in high-concurrency environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/blog/2023-09-06-graphql-vs-rest.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// This call assigns the Task to the current user
// IF AND ONLY IF the the task has not been modified on the server
await medplum.patchResource('Task', task.id, [
  { op: 'test', path: '/meta/versionId', value: task.meta?.versionId },
  { op: 'replace', path: '/status', value: 'accepted' },
  { op: 'replace', path: '/owner', value: createReference(currentUser) },
]);
```

