TITLE: SQL Query with Multiple Values for a Search Parameter
DESCRIPTION: Shows the SQL query for `Observation?_profile=http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-observation-lab,http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-observation-social-history`.  The `&&` operator is used to match if arrays have any element in common.  The search parameter `_profile` has multiple values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/contributing/search-architecture.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT "Observation"."id", "Observation"."content" FROM "Observation"
WHERE ("Observation"."deleted"=false AND (
  -- && matches if arrays have any element in common
  "Observation"."_profile" IS NOT NULL AND "Observation"."_profile" && ARRAY[
    'http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-observation-lab',
    'http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-observation-social-history'
  ]::TEXT[]
))
```

