TITLE: Customizing Token Lifetimes (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to customize token lifetimes using the `ClientApplication` resource. It involves updating the resource with desired access and refresh token lifetimes (in seconds).  It requires familiarity with the Medplum API and `ClientApplication` resource.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/auth/session-management.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const tokenLifetimes = async (): Promise<void> => {
  // 1. Read the ClientApplication resource.
  const client = await medplum.readResource('ClientApplication', 'CLIENT_ID');

  // 2. Update the ClientApplication resource.
  const result = await medplum.updateResource<Medplum.ClientApplication>({
    ...client,
    accessTokenLifespan: 7200, // 2 hours
    refreshTokenLifespan: 2419200, // 4 weeks
  });

  console.log('ClientApplication', result);
};

```

