TITLE: GraphQL Query for Diagnostic Reports Turnaround Time
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query retrieves DiagnosticReport data including issue date, category, code, specimen details (collection and received times), and subject (patient) information to calculate turnaround time for tests. It requires access to Medplum's GraphQL endpoint and assumes familiarity with the FHIR data model. The query filters DiagnosticReports issued after '2023-02-01' and returns a maximum of 100 results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/compliance/clia-cap.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
{
  DiagnosticReportConnection(
    issued: \"gt2023-02-01\"
    _count: 100
  ) {
    count
    edges {
      resource {
        id
        issued
        category {
          coding {
            code
          }
        }
        code {
          coding {
            code
          }
        }
        specimen {
          resource {
            ... on Specimen {
              collection {
                collectedDateTime
              }
              receivedTime
            }
          }
        }
        subject {
          resource {
            ... on Patient {
              id
              gender
              address {
                state
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

