TITLE: Using Subscription Extensions with `useSubscription` (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use subscription extensions to filter events based on the type of interaction (e.g., 'create'). It shows how to pass the `subscriptionProps` option to the `useSubscription` hook to specify the desired extensions, allowing you to listen for specific types of resource interactions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/react/use-subscription.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const createOnlyOptions = {
  subscriptionProps: {
    extension: [
      {
        url: 'https://medplum.com/fhir/StructureDefinition/subscription-supported-interaction',
        valueCode: 'create',
      },
    ],
  },
};

function MyComponent(): JSX.Element {
  const [createCount, setCreateCount] = useState(0);

  useSubscription(
    'Communication?sender=Practitioner/abc-123&recipient=Practitioner/me-456',
    (_bundle) => {
      console.log('Received a new message from Practitioner/abc-123!');
      setCreateCount((s) => s + 1);
    },
    createOnlyOptions
  );

  return <div>Create notifications received: {createCount}</div>;
}
```

