TITLE: SQL Query for Organization by Profile and Active Status
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the SQL query generated for the FHIR search `Organization?_profile=http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-organization&active=true`.  It demonstrates how array columns and boolean filters are handled in the SQL query. The `&&` operator checks for overlap between arrays and multiple search parameters are ANDed together.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/contributing/search-architecture.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT "Organization"."id", "Organization"."content" FROM "Organization"
WHERE ("Organization"."deleted"=false AND (
  -- && operator checks for overlap between arrays
  ("Organization"."_profile" IS NOT NULL AND "Organization"."_profile" && ARRAY[
    'http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-organization'
  ]::TEXT[])
  -- Multiple search parameters are ANDed together in the SQL query
  AND "Organization"."active"=true
))
```

