TITLE: Estimating Total Storage Size
DESCRIPTION: This formula calculates the total storage required based on resource count, patient total, average size, average history length, and an overhead factor. It provides a way to estimate the database size for a Medplum self-hosted instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/blog/2023-03-28-estimating-rds-size.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
totalStorage = resourceCount * patientTotal * avgSize * avgHistoryLength / (1024 * 1024) * (1 + overheadFactor)
```

