TITLE: Artillery Configuration for FHIR Datastore Load Test (YAML)
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration file defines the target URL, test phases (warm-up and ramp-up), and variables (authentication token) for load testing a FHIR datastore. It also defines a scenario for creating, reading, and searching Patient resources.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/self-hosting/load-testing.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: YAML
CODE:
```
config:
  target: 'https://api.staging.medplum.com'
  phases:
    - duration: 10
      arrivalRate: 10
      name: Warm up
    - duration: 60
      arrivalRate: 10
      rampTo: 50
      name: Ramp up load
  variables:
    auth: 'Bearer MY_ACCESS_TOKEN'

scenarios:
  - name: 'FHIR Datastore'
    flow:
      - loop:
          - post:
              url: '/fhir/R4/Patient'
              headers:
                Authorization: '{{ auth }}'
              json:
                resourceType: Patient
                name:
                  - family: '{{ $randomString() }}'
              capture:
                - json: '$.id'
                  as: 'patientId'
                - json: '$.name[0].family'
                  as: 'familyName'
          - get:
              url: '/fhir/R4/Patient/{{ patientId }}'
              headers:
                Authorization: '{{ auth }}'
          - get:
              url: '/fhir/R4/Patient?name={{ familyName }}'
              headers:
                Authorization: '{{ auth }}'
        count: 10
```

