TITLE: Using the useSubscription Hook
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the `useSubscription` hook to subscribe to FHIR search criteria and receive real-time notifications. The hook creates an in-memory `Subscription` resource and calls the provided callback function when a matching event occurs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/react-hooks/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
function MyComponent(): JSX.Element {
  const [notificationCount, setNotificationCount] = useState(0);

  useSubscription('Communication?sender=Practitioner/abc-123&recipient=Practitioner/me-456', (bundle: Bundle) => {
    console.log('Received a message from Practitioner/abc-123!');
    handleNotificationBundle(bundle); // Do something with the bundle
    setNotificationCount((s) => s + 1);
  });

  return <div>Notifications received: {notificationCount}</div>;
}
```

