TITLE: Testing Bot Idempotency in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates how to test a Bot for idempotency by calling the bot twice and ensuring that no resources are created or updated during the second call.  It utilizes Jest's `spyOn` to monitor client interactions. The test calls the bot twice and verifies no additional resources are created on the second call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/bots/unit-testing-bots.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { MockClient } from '@medplum/mock';
import { handler } from './my-bot';

test('Idempotency test', async () => {
  const medplum = new MockClient();
  const createResourceSpy = jest.spyOn(medplum, 'createResource');
  const updateResourceSpy = jest.spyOn(medplum, 'updateResource');

  // First call
  await handler(medplum, {});

  // Second call
  await handler(medplum, {});

  expect(createResourceSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  expect(updateResourceSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
});
```

