TITLE: Querying Linked FHIR Resources with GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query retrieves a Patient resource by ID, including their name and address. It then retrieves a list of DiagnosticReport resources related to the patient and Observation resources referenced by the DiagnosticReport.result field. It showcases the ability to fetch nested and linked resources in a single query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/blog/2023-09-06-graphql-vs-rest.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
{
  Patient(id: "patient-id") {
    name {
      given
      family
    }
    address {
      line
      city
      state
      postalCode
    }
    # highlight-start
    # Get all DiagnosticReports related to this patient
    DiagnosticReportList(_reference: patient) {
      # highlight-end
      performer {
        reference
      }
      code {
        text
      }
      # highlight-start
      # Get all Observation resources
      # referenced by DiagnosticReport.result
      result {
        resource {
          ... on Observation {
            status
            code {
              text
            }
            valueQuantity {
              value
              unit
            }
          }
        }
      }
      # highlight-end
    }
  }
}
```

