TITLE: Validating CodeSystem Codes SQL
DESCRIPTION: Validates whether a CodeSystem contains any of a set of codes. First, it retrieves the CodeSystem ID based on the URL. Then, it checks if the codes exist in the Coding table for the specified CodeSystem ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/contributing/terminology-architecture.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
-- Get CodeSystem by URL
SELECT id, content FROM "CodeSystem" WHERE url = ?;

-- Check whether codes exist
SELECT id, code, display FROM "Coding"
WHERE code IN (?, ?) AND system = ?;
```

