TITLE: Token Exchange Request with cURL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to exchange an external access token for a Medplum access token using a cURL command. It requires setting the grant_type, client_id, subject_token, and subject_token_type parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/auth/methods/token-exchange.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: cURL
CODE:
```
curl -X POST \
  'https://api.medplum.com/oauth2/token' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  -d 'grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange' \
  -d 'client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID' \
  -d 'subject_token=YOUR_SUBJECT_TOKEN' \
  -d 'subject_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token'
```

