TITLE: Importing Definitions and Indexing Schema for MockClient in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to import FHIR schema definitions and index the full schema within your testing setup using `beforeAll` or a setup file. This is essential for ensuring that your test queries work correctly with the `MockClient` in Medplum Bots.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/bots/unit-testing-bots.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { indexStructureDefinitionBundles } from '@medplum/core';
import { readJson } from '@medplum/definitions';
import { MockClient } from '@medplum/mock';

let medplum: MockClient;

beforeAll(() => {
  indexStructureDefinitionBundles(Object.values(readJson('fhir/r4/profiles-resources.json') as Record<string, any>));
  indexStructureDefinitionBundles(Object.values(readJson('fhir/r4/profiles-types.json') as Record<string, any>));
  indexStructureDefinitionBundles(Object.values(readJson('fhir/r4/profiles-others.json') as Record<string, any>));

  medplum = new MockClient();
});
```

