TITLE: Incorrect FHIR Batch Upsert with UUID References (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates an incorrect approach to performing FHIR batch upserts using UUID references in the URL.  The `urn:uuid:` syntax for internal references is not allowed in the `Bundle.entry.request.url` for a conditional update within a batch. The `CareTeam` resource incorrectly references the `Patient` resource using its UUID in the URL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/fhir-datastore/fhir-batch-requests.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
{
  "resourceType": "Bundle",
  "type": "batch",
  "entry": [
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:4410cb87-4a38-4d3f-bee8-3c3556e6debc",
      "request": {
        "method": "PUT",
        "url": "Patient?identifier=http://example.com/mrn|1234567"
      },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Patient",
        "identifier": [{ "system": "http://example.com/mrn", "value": "1234567" }]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:b122a53c-9c0d-4654-9260-c0b67b7bc5d4",
      "request": {
        "method": "PUT",
        // Incorrect: Upsert URL cannot use replaced urn:uuid: syntax
        "url": "CareTeam?subject=urn:uuid:4410cb87-4a38-4d3f-bee8-3c3556e6debc"
      },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "CareTeam",
        "subject": { "reference": "urn:uuid:4410cb87-4a38-4d3f-bee8-3c3556e6debc" }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

