TITLE: SQL Query for FHIR Token Search with NOT Modifier
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query implements a FHIR search for DiagnosticReport resources, specifically handling the 'code:not' modifier. It joins the DiagnosticReport table with a token table and uses a WHERE clause to exclude resources that have a matching token value, effectively implementing the 'not' modifier.
SOURCE: https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/main/packages/docs/docs/contributing/search-architecture.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
SELECT "DiagnosticReport"."id", "DiagnosticReport"."content" FROM "DiagnosticReport"
  LEFT JOIN "DiagnosticReport_Token" AS "T1" ON (
    "DiagnosticReport"."id"="T1"."resourceId" AND
    -- Tokens are stored essentially as (searchParam, system, code) tuples
    "T1"."code"='code' AND (
      "T1"."system"='http://loinc.org' AND
      "T1"."value"='69737-5'
    )
  )
WHERE ("DiagnosticReport"."deleted"=false AND
  -- Negate the search and find rows that do NOT match
  "T1"."resourceId" IS NULL
) GROUP BY "DiagnosticReport"."id"
```

